        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='8471' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='8' type-v2='text' w='24636' x='71818' y='27412'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>While some regions see parity, others highlight a persistent gender gap in key white-collar sectors.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='10588' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='27182' x='69273' y='30824'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Finance, Real Estate, and Tech expanded regionally, but is this growth tied to formal education?</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='11000' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='5' type-v2='text' w='27688' x='69438' y='32000'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>This map shows which regions are most reliant on degree-heavy sectors like health, education, and professional services.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='8471' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='4' type-v2='text' w='33273' x='9000' y='25059'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Some industries grew despite—or perhaps because of—their distance from formal academic pathways.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='12706' hidden='true' id='11' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='24364' x='10455' y='20588'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Younger generations are leaning more toward service and tech-related sectors, hinting at evolving career values.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='20000' hidden='true' id='12' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='15563' x='82688' y='43778'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Over a decade, some industries saw growth while others declined—revealing shifting demand and possibly automation impacts.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='11294' hidden='true' id='13' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='33273' x='8818' y='24471'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>In 2011, male dominance was evident in traditionally manual sectors, while education and healthcare saw higher female participation.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='14706' id='14' story-point-id='9' type-v2='text' w='21455' x='61545' y='23529'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>AI-susceptible roles are seeing varied growth—prompting questions about the stability of knowledge jobs.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
